A commercial organization that provides weather forecasts on demand to subscribers.
The forecast faxed to the Scandia spanned the period from Thursday, January 18, to Sunday, January 21.
The main deck of the Scandia inside the engineroom was called the fidley deck; the engineroom space above it was called the fidley, and the space below was the lower engineroom, where the propulsion engine was located.
The fidley deck consisted of a steel grating over the engine, surrounded by steel deck plating.
