The vessel's electrical distribution systems, switchboards, and transformers were in the fidley.
A watertight steel door at the aft end of the fidley led to the exterior of the main deck aft, where the winch for towing barges was.
Emergency remote controls for shutting off fuel pumps to the propulsion and generator engines were on a bulkhead just outside the fidley's aft door, along with remote controls for closing the valves from the fuel tanks.
Also located here were the control switches for the engineroom ventilation supply fans and exhaust fans.
