Company Training and Drills Company representatives stated that the EMC's vessel crews received on-site training in drug and alcohol awareness, benzene handling, and tank barge vapor-recovery systems.
Employees were also trained at the U.S. Merchant Marine Academy, New York, in survival at sea and in vapor-recovery systems.
The company did not, and was not required to, train its employees at marine firefighting school.
